17/07/2005
SARAJEVO, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- The BiH Presidency decided on Friday (15 July) on activities related to the upcoming 10th anniversary of the Dayton Peace Agreement.
The decision envisions commemorative events held in Washington on 21 November, on 14 December in Paris, and on 21 December in Sarajevo.
The tripartite presidency plans to discuss the plan with ambassadors of all countries that signed the Accords.
In other news, the Bosniak member of the BiH Presidency, Sulejman Tihic, said Friday that the BiH Defence Reform Commission would sign an official agreement on the new BiH defence law Monday.
The bill would be then forwarded to the entity and central parliaments in BiH for approval.
The draft envisions the establishment of a single army, chain of command and financing from the state budget.
The entity ministries of defence will be abolished early next year.
(Nezavisne novine, Fena, RTRS - 16/07/05;
Fena - 15/07/05)
